Mikołaj Małkiński

March 7, 2019

The task is to: Narysowac mape Europy (filter(long > -30, lat > 30)) z wyszczegolnionymi krajami, podpisac kazdy kraj i w nawiasie napisac ile ma nuts poziomu 1, np “PL 7”.

library('ggplot2')
library('dplyr')
library('eurostat')
library('mapproj')

lp <- get_eurostat_geospatial(output_class = 'df', resolution = '60', nuts_level = 'all')
names_df <- filter(lp, LEVL_CODE == 0) %>%
  group_by(NUTS_NAME) %>% 
  summarise(long = mean(long), lat = mean(lat))


lp %>%
  filter(long > -30 & lat > 30) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = long, y = lat, group = group, fill = CNTR_CODE)) +
  geom_polygon(color = "black") +
  geom_text(data = names_df, aes(x = long, y = lat, label = NUTS_NAME), inherit.aes = FALSE) +
  coord_map()
